caption: Attribute Dictionary
description: The Attribute Dictionary defines schema attributes and includes references to the events and objects in which they are used.
name: dictionary

cc.caption: Cc
cc.description: The users having their email address in Cc values, as defined by RFC 5322.

delivered_to.caption: Delivered To
delivered_to.description: The user having email address in Delivered-To email header field.

entity_type_id.caption: Entity Type ID
entity_type_id.description: The type of entity or object.

from.caption: From
from.description: The user having email address in email header From values, as defined by RFC 5322.

raw_data.caption: Raw Data
raw_data.description: The event data as received from the event source.

record_id.description: Unique identifier for record or event
record_id.caption: Record ID

reply_to.caption: Reply To
reply_to.description: The user having email address in the email header Reply-To values, as defined by RFC 5322.

to.caption: To
to.description: The users having email address in the email header To values, as defined by RFC 5322.
